[3] Canada (Manitoba)
Date: Thu 17 Apr 2014
Source: CBC (Canadian Broadcasting Corporation) News [edited]
http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/manitoba-confirms-5th-case-of-measles-1.2612808


Manitoba health officials have reported a 5th case of measles, this time involving a man in his 20s living in the Winnipeg area.

The latest case was announced via Twitter on Wednesday [16 Apr 2014]. Manitoba Health is warning people who visited the Bison Medical Walk-In Clinic on [11 Apr 2014] between 10 am and 10:30 am that they might have been exposed to measles.

If you were at this location and think you may have had contact with someone with measles, the province is asking you to call your doctor or Health Links at 204-788-8200 or 1-888-315-9257 (toll-free) for more information.

