[6] USA ex Chile (Magellan and Chilean Antarctica Region)
Date: Fri 18 Apr 2014
Source: Radiopolar.com [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
http://radiopolar.com/noticia_88106.html


Last Thu 17 Apr 2014, the Regional Ministerial Secretariat of Health [SEREMI] was notified of a measles case in an American citizen who had visited the town of Puerto Williams recently. The case was diagnosed when the tourist returned to her country of origin.

Following this information, the Magellan SEREMI of Health, Oscar Vargas, reported that the Epidemiology Unit has activated the monitoring system in order to identify the persons who came in contact with the tourist during her travel in the region and, at the same time, perform an active search for consultations to emergency services and public and private medical practices from February [2014] until the current date; for this purpose, contact with the entire regional network will be established.

The health authority was emphatic in pointing out that Chile is a measles-free country, in accordance with government policies carried out by the Ministry of Health, for the benefit and protection of the population. Currently this vaccine is part of the National Immunization Program schedule for infants and [again] in 1st grade of school. This shows the importance of parents keeping up the vaccination schedule for their children as a 1st step in protecting them.

It is worth mentioning that in the coming days, on the occasion of the 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil [12 Jun-13 Jul 2014], the Ministry of Health will be calling on the population traveling to this event and who were born between 1971 and 1981 to be vaccinated against measles.

