[8] Viet Nam
Date: Wed 16 Apr 2014
Source: Voice of Viet Nam [edited]
http://english.vov.vn/Society/Prime-Ministers-telegram-to-tackle-measles/275468.vov


On [16 Apr 2014], Prime Minister Nguyen Tan Dung sent an important telegram urging ministries, agencies, and localities to take tough new measures to prevent the spread of measles and minimise fatalities.

Since December 2013, 3126 out of 8441 suspected cases were diagnosed with the disease in 61 provinces and cities nationwide, claiming 25 lives. Most measles patients had not received an immunization against the disease.

The government leader asked the Health Ministry to timely diagnose and provide treatment for infected cases to reduce fatalities. He called for sufficient supply of vaccines, drugs and medical equipment to save measles patients and control the spread of the disease. He requested leaders of provinces and centrally-run cities to coordinate closely with the Health Ministry to take necessary quarantine measures, give measles vaccination to high-risk groups, and grant financial assistance to patients in need. PM Dung also directed the Ministry of Information and Communications and media agencies to update information on measles and raise public awareness of the potential danger of the disease.

--
Communicated by:
PRO/MBDS
<promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[The newswires above update the measles situation in Viet Nam. It seems that the situation is worse than was reported before. Though the reported numbers are inconsistent, the most up to date media reports show that more than 7000 measles cases have been reported from 61 out of 63 provinces in Viet Nam since the beginning of 2014, and among those, 108 cases died.

As explained by the Minister of Health, most severe, complicated cases have been transferred to the National Pediatric Hospital, which makes the reported number of deaths related to measles from the hospital high. There has been no detailed epidemiological information on measles by province.

The decision of whether to announce a measles epidemic falls to the provincial authorities, not the Ministry of Health or the national government. Although there is no official announcement of a measles epidemic from any of the provinces, the Prime Minister has sent an urgent telegram to ask all provinces to strengthen their measures to suppress the measles outbreak.

For a map of Viet Nam with provinces, see http://www.onlineasiatravel.com/images/vn/vietnam-map.png. For the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map with direct links to other outbreaks in Viet Nam and surrounding countries reported on ProMED-mail and PRO/MBDS, see https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2420132,152. - Mod.QCN]
